     2→ * MMS PM Scheduler Service - Tactical PM Scheduling
     3→ *
     4→ * Schedules preventive maintenance within a 12-week horizon, respecting:
     5→ * - Compliance windows (mileage OR time triggers)
     6→ * - PM hierarchy (C4 satisfies C1/C2/C3)
     7→ * - Track capability requirements
     8→ * - Material constraints (hard 14 days, soft 90 days)
     9→ * - Maximo lock status (INPRG work orders are read-only)
    10→ * - Service demand (fleet availability)
    11→ *
    12→ * Key business rules:
    13→ * - Compliance window: ±10% of interval (mileage or months)
    14→ * - PM hierarchy: Higher-level PMs satisfy lower-level requirements
    15→ * - Material hard constraint: BLOCKING parts must be available within 14 days
    16→ * - Material soft constraint: Warning if parts unavailable within 90 days
    17→ * - Track utilization target: 85%
    18→ * - Maximo lock: Cannot modify PM with INPRG work order
    19→ *
    20→ * @see specs/003-database-schema.md Section 3.5 (PM Management)
    21→ * @see specs/004-domain-services.md Section 4.4 (PM Scheduler)
